## 2. Detailed Column Lists & Table Dictionary

### 1. `users` Table
Handles authenticating normal customers and store owners. Location added for proximity search.
| Column Name | Type | Key | Remarks |
|---|---|---|---|
| `user_id` | INT | **PK** | Auto-incremented unique ID |
| `name` | VARCHAR(100) | | Full name |
| `email` | VARCHAR(100) | Unique | Used for login |
| `phone` | VARCHAR(20) | | Contact number |
| `password_hash` | VARCHAR(255) | | Encrypted password string |
| `role` | ENUM | | `CUSTOMER` or `STORE_OWNER` |
| `latitude` | DECIMAL(10,8) | | GPS location (up to 8 decimal precision) |
| `longitude` | DECIMAL(11,8) | | GPS location (up to 8 decimal precision) |
| `created_at` | TIMESTAMP | | Record insertion time |

### 2. `stores` Table
Owned by users. The flattened table absorbs specific address breakdown, operating hours, and cover images from the 11-table spec.
| Column Name | Type | Key | Remarks |
|---|---|---|---|
| `store_id` | INT | **PK** | Auto-incremented unique ID |
| `owner_id` | INT | **FK** | References `users(user_id)` |
| `store_name` | VARCHAR(150) | | Registered business name |
| `description` | TEXT | | Details about the shop |
| `address_line1` | VARCHAR(200) | | Primary location data |
| `city` | VARCHAR(100) | | Searchable city |
| `state` | VARCHAR(100) | | Regional boundary |
| `pincode` | VARCHAR(10) | | Postal code |
| `contact_number` | VARCHAR(20) | | Store's direct line |
| `opening_time` | TIME | | Normal daily shift start |
| `closing_time` | TIME | | Normal daily shift end |
| `latitude` | DECIMAL(10,8) | | Store GPS for 5km Haversine math |
| `longitude` | DECIMAL(11,8) | | Store GPS |
| `image_url` | VARCHAR(255) | | Cover photo for the storefront |
| `is_active` | BOOLEAN | | Is the store currently open for business? (Default: TRUE) |
| `created_at` | TIMESTAMP | | Record insertion time |

### 3. `products` Table
Inventory items. By removing the variants / images / category tables, we store the sku, size, color, string category, and stock quantity directly inside the product row.
| Column Name | Type | Key | Remarks |
|---|---|---|---|
| `product_id` | INT | **PK** | Auto-incremented unique ID |
| `store_id` | INT | **FK** | References `stores(store_id)` |
| `product_name` | VARCHAR(150) | | Clothing title |
| `brand` | VARCHAR(100) | | Brand identity |
| `category` | VARCHAR(100) | | E.g. "Men's Tops", "Shoes" |
| `size` | VARCHAR(10) | | Absorbed from variants e.g. "XL", "M", "42" |
| `color` | VARCHAR(50) | | Absorbed from variants e.g. "Navy Blue" |
| `sku` | VARCHAR(100) | Unique | Stock Keeping Unit |
| `price` | DECIMAL(10,2) | | Full price of the item |
| `quantity` | INT | | Available stock (Absorbed from `inventory`) |
| `description` | TEXT | | Product details |
| `image_url` | VARCHAR(255) | | Primary product photo (Absorbed from `images`) |
| `is_active` | BOOLEAN | | (Default: TRUE) |
| `created_at` | TIMESTAMP | | Record insertion time |

### 4. `orders` Table
Captures pre-orders. By flattening `order_items`, an order assumes the purchase of a single type of `product_id`, capturing the price splitting directly.
| Column Name | Type | Key | Remarks |
|---|---|---|---|
| `order_id` | INT | **PK** | Auto-incremented unique ID |
| `user_id` | INT | **FK** | The customer: References `users(user_id)` |
| `store_id` | INT | **FK** | The physical store: References `stores(store_id)` |
| `product_id` | INT | **FK** | The preordered item: References `products(product_id)` |
| `quantity` | INT | | How many of this product are they reserving? |
| `total_amount` | DECIMAL(10,2)| | Full checkout value `(price * quantity)` |
| `advance_amount`| DECIMAL(10,2)| | The required 20% down payment |
| `balance_amount`| DECIMAL(10,2)| | What remains to be paid at the physical store |
| `order_status` | ENUM | | `PENDING`, `RESERVED` (advance paid), `COMPLETED` (picked up), `CANCELLED` |
| `payment_status`| ENUM | | `PENDING`, `PARTIAL` (advance paid), `PAID` (balance cleared) |
| `order_date` | TIMESTAMP | | When the preorder was initiated |
| `notes` | TEXT | | Customer requests ("Will arrive by 6 PM")|

### 5. `payments` Table
Captures the financial transaction data for the 20% advance or the settlement.
| Column Name | Type | Key | Remarks |
|---|---|---|---|
| `payment_id` | INT | **PK** | Auto-incremented unique ID |
| `order_id` | INT | **FK** | References `orders(order_id)` |
| `user_id` | INT | **FK** | References `users(user_id)` |
| `amount` | DECIMAL(10,2) | | Exact money transferred |
| `payment_method`| ENUM | | `CARD`, `UPI`, `NET_BANKING`, `CASH` (at store) |
| `type` | ENUM | | `ADVANCE` (the initial 20%), `SETTLEMENT` (the final 80%) |
| `status` | ENUM | | `SUCCESS`, `FAILED`, `PENDING` |
| `gateway_ref_id`| VARCHAR(150) | | Receipt ID from Razorpay / Stripe etc. |
| `payment_date` | TIMESTAMP | | When funds cleared |

### 6. `admins` Table
Distinct table for top-level MNC platform management safely separated from `users`.
| Column Name | Type | Key | Remarks |
|---|---|---|---|
| `admin_id` | INT | **PK** | Auto-incremented unique ID |
| `name` | VARCHAR(100) | | Full name of admin |
| `email` | VARCHAR(100) | Unique | Secure login |
| `password_hash` | VARCHAR(255) | | Encrypted password |
| `role` | ENUM | | `SUPER_ADMIN`, `MODERATOR` |
| `created_at` | TIMESTAMP | | Record insertion time |

